tter Think About Herd Immunity </a></h2>   <p class="o-dek c-feature__dek">It turns out the number is largely up to us.</p>   <div class="o-meta c-feature__meta"><ul class="o-meta__byline">  <li class="o-meta__author"><a href="https://www.theatlantic.com/author/caroline-mimbs-nyce/">Caroline Mimbs Nyce</a></li>  </ul></div>  </div></article>  <div class="l-hp-top__off-off-lede-stack">  <article class="c-story-strip c-story-strip--off-off-lede-stack"  id="hp-lowerbelt-1"  ><div class="c-story-strip__content">  <h2 class="o-hed c-story-strip__hed"><a class="c-story-strip__hed-link" href="https://www.theatlantic.com/ideas/archive/2020/07/how-corrupt-justice-department/614098/"> How to Corrupt the Justice Department </a></h2>   <div class="o-meta c-story-strip__meta"><ul class="o-meta__byline">  <li class="o-meta__author"><a href="https://www.theatlantic.com/author/quinta-jurecic/">Quinta Jurecic</a></li>  <li class="o-meta__author"><a href="https://www.theatlantic.com/author/benjamin-wittes/">Benjamin Wittes</a></li>  </ul></div>  </div>  <div class="c-story-strip__image"><figure class="o-media c-story-strip__media"><a class="o-media__object" href="https://www.theatlantic.com/ideas/archive/2020/07/how-corrupt-justice-department/614098/"><picture><img class="o-media__img u-lazy--img lazyload" data-srcset="https://cdn.theatlantic.com/thumbor/1JHrHlFUQowFchS44WUC9OXYBmQ=/436x0:1561x1125/86x86/filters:format(png)/media/img/mt/2020/07/Atlantic_justice_corrupt_v1/original.png, https://cdn.theatlantic.com/thumbor/5LyI53fLJyMY2KQGU_6KDEFnhyI=/436x0:1561x1125/172x172/filters:format(png)/media/img/mt/2020/07/Atlantic_justice_corrupt_v1/original.png 2x" alt="An illustration of the scales of justice transformed into a marionette"></picture></a><noscript><img class="o-media__img u-object-cover" src="https://cdn.theatlantic.com/thumbor/1JHrHlFUQowFchS44WUC9OXYBmQ=/436x0:1561x1125/86x86/filters:format(png)/media/img/mt/2020/07/Atlantic_justice_corrupt_v1/original.png" alt="An illustr